"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody. In my opinion, beneficial bacteria will have a greater long-term effect than probiotic bacteria, and that has biodiversity. Your bacteria is unique to you and you have to regrow it. You don't replenish it. This is a little bit of a myth that you just add beneficial bacteria or probiotic bacteria and it replenishes your gut bacteria. No, you have to actually regrow your bacteria because it's so unique to you, and it uses all the biospace of you. And one of the things that bacteria does is it shares genes with each other, basically shares tools with each other to get its job done. And this is where the millions and trillions of different types of bacteria that's formed, that's found in beneficial bacteria, does a better job in that it has more tools for your gut to use. If you can imagine probiotic bacteria is like a newspaper with one letter repeated over and over and over again, while beneficial bacteria has millions of different stories that it tells. Anyway, part four coming up.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 1.28,\n      \"duration\": 0.96,\n      \"confidence\": 0.985,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.998\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          